      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SUNSET HILL NZ (5) is a progressive trotter who will be be fitter for two starts since a spell, leading from a couple of spots wider on Tuesday before boxing on to go under by 1.2m. Building good statistics both here and at the distance and could be ready to show his best third up. I AM HELLBOUND (1) is also on the back up after proving too strong for Sunset Hill on Tuesday. Deserved that win following a string of placings and the ace draw gives him the chance to deliver again. SHEZA CHANCE (6) hasn't raced since placing at Group 3 level in Brisbane in December but is a three-time fresh winner who will be ready to go off a trial win. MISTER BLINDSIDE (3) bombed the start on Tuesday but beat I AM HELLBOUND in winning at this circuit and distance prior so is worth another chance. French import KRISTAL JOSSELYN (9) has switched to Luke McCarthy since last seen. Yet to make an impact in Australia but will strip fitter and is capable of much better.",
